      "issue": "The prompt referred to an underlined idea even though the plain-text item did not mark any text as underlined, creating an avoidable accessibility and rendering ambiguity.",
      "change": "Rephrased the stem to ask explicitly for a word or phrase with the opposite meaning of expand while preserving the keyed answer and answer position."
    },
    {
      "itemId": "parapro-b4-reading-021",
      "issue": "The feedback for kite described /k/ as produced in a similar way to the initial sound in giant, an unnecessary and potentially inaccurate phonological characterization.",
      "change": "Replaced the statement with a direct, accurate comparison that /k/ does not match the initial /j/ sound in giant."
    },
    {
      "itemId": "parapro-b4-reading-031",
      "issue": "The original homophone item was framed as correcting a student's written spelling error, which fit the writing domain more closely than the current ParaPro reading-application scope; one distractor was also implausibly based on word length.",
